pr_title: Change from LunrJs to MinisearchJs for client-side search
pr_body: This PR aims to close Issue #2141.
pr_review_comments:

pr_body:
_Edit by @mortenpi: added the TODO list:_
_Last Edit by @Hetarth02 : 2023-08-20:_

- [x] Have the modal be full size all the time on desktop too.
- [x] Distinguish the `search-result-title` somehow (`font-weigth: 600`).
- [x] Have the `search-result-title` for code items (like function names and such; anything except `Page`, `Section`) in monospace (but make font a bit smaller, to match what we do in main body).
- [x] Add section titles to search results (add to the bottom near the URL somehow).
- [x] Fix the bug with some URLs incorrectly being cut off (search "parametric")
- [x] Remove / replace the "No recent searches!" string, as it's confusing. Replace with `Type something to get started`.
- [x] Get rid of the search input box (or make it inactive, with click triggering the search modal)

_Edit by @mortenpi:_ close #1437, close #2147

---

Well, the search UI has had a complete overhaul, with a fresh new modal UI s mentioned in Issue #2147 with better context for search results and a filter mechanism to remove those pesky unwanted results.

Here is the full demo,

https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/80420115/ad7ebc4e-4148-49b6-ba53-8a3baa39cea8


- Additionally, the modal is mobile responsive!

Search will now look like this,

### Light Mode:
Without Filter:
![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/80420115/978f9086-c251-456c-9716-ef256c006a8f)

With Filter: 
![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/80420115/e1626918-05a8-4499-b8f0-83bb6a83c109)

### Dark Mode:
Without Filter:
![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/80420115/a4ca7595-02b8-4fe8-b5d8-ba97aff98ed5)

With Filter: 
![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/80420115/1158f494-545e-4a5f-89a6-49a1fe1acba6)

~Since these we very small fixes, I did them while we are updating the search UI altogether.~
~- #2215 Removed some extra space between navbar header icons.~
![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/80420115/9ce4cbe2-2a2d-4989-8690-bf551f9e6613)

~- #2103: Fixed, docstring collapse/expand icon not changing when clicking rapidly. Now click all you want!~
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 1299591278, 'comment_body': "I don't see why we wouldn't want to fill up pretty much the whole vertical space? I was thinking maybe we could do about `margin-top/bottom` instead of `max-height`, but this would work too:

```suggestion
  max-height: calc(100vh - 15rem);
```

![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/147757/e78c3bc0-d1ee-4d43-80f7-1109921c22ab)
![image](https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl/assets/147757/ae886079-bb35-4dfa-bda6-396495d3b74a)

", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 21, 4, 37, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mortenpi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1299592357, 'comment_body': "This applies to multiple places, but let's not use `px` units, but instead use `rem` (except for like borders, shadows, rounded corners and such). Among other things, that (should be) consistent with how the rest of SCSS is written.

Also, this should be the equivalent of `14px` (to be consistent with the main body). We can probably just replicate the `rem`s of the main body (there should be a variable for that).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 21, 4, 40, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mortenpi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1299593059, 'comment_body': "We can leave this as is, but in general I am not a fan of these kinds of helpers -- essentially you're using HTML to do the styling again.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 21, 4, 42, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mortenpi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1299593672, 'comment_body': "Semantically, wouldn't a `<button>` be more suitable here?

Also, let's merge all the CSS into `#documenter-search-query`. I don't think we reuse `.docs-search-query` anywhere?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 21, 4, 44, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mortenpi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1299597994, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
* The search UI has had a complete overhaul, with a fresh new modal UI with better context for search results and a filter mechanism to remove unwanted results. The client-side search engine has been changed from LunrJs to MinisearchJs. ([#2141], [#2147])
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 21, 4, 54, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'mortenpi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1300559779, 'comment_body': 'I find these kinds of helper more useful, maybe it has to do something with me using bootstrap normally...', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 21, 19, 32, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Hetarth02', 'type': 'User'}]
